            <h2>How to Cancel Air France Ticket?</h2>
            <p>You can cancel the Air France ticket by visiting the official website or the mobile app of the airline. Yes, once you visit the airline's official website, then you can log in with your details and enter the booking number. Now, navigate to the section "My Bookings" and select the flight that you want to cancel and wish to receive the refund. Once the cancellation is completed, then, you can get the full refund to the same source of payments if your ticket is eligible for the refund.</p>
            <h3>What about the 24-hour cancellation rule?</h3>
            <p>Passengers can be entitled to a full refund for the ticket if they cancel the ticket within 24 hours of reservation, no matter their ticket type. You need to submit a refund request to claim the refund, and after the cancellation process, the refund will automatically be issued to your source account. You need to mention the required details such as booking reference and the personal information.</p>
            <h2>Summary</h2>
            <p>Air France offers a flexible refund policy for flight cancellations. Passengers can receive refunds in the form of miles, credits for future travel, or direct transfers to their bank account. To get a full refund, tickets must be cancelled within 24 hours of booking.</p>
            <p>Refund requests can be managed online via the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/air-france.aspx"><b>Air France</b></a> website, where passengers can log in to view their cancellation and refund status. For additional assistance, Air France's 24/7 customer service is available to guide passengers through the process. Alternatively, travellers can work with third-party agencies to ensure smooth and hassle-free refund management.</p>
            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>How can I cancel my Air France ticket?</h3>
            <p>To cancel your Air France ticket:</p>
            <p>- Visit the Air France official website or mobile app.</p>
            <p>- Log in to your account using your details.</p>
            <p>- Go to the "My Bookings" section.</p>
            <p>- Select the flight you wish to cancel and complete the process.</p>
            <p>- Once canceled, eligible refunds will be credited to the original payment method.</p>
            <h3>What is Air France’s 24-hour cancellation rule?</h3>
            <p>Air France allows passengers to cancel their tickets within 24 hours of booking for a full refund, regardless of the ticket type. Passengers must submit a refund request to initiate the process. After cancellation, the refund will be automatically issued to the original payment method.</p>
            <h3>Can I get a refund for a non-refundable ticket on Air France?</h3>
            <p>Non-refundable tickets are generally not eligible for monetary refunds. However, Air France may provide travel credits or miles for future use, depending on the circumstances and ticket type.</p>
            <h3>How long does it take to process an Air France refund?</h3>
            <p>Refunds are typically processed within 7–20 business days for payments made via credit card or bank transfer. Refunds in the form of travel credits are often issued more quickly.</p>
            <h3>Who should I contact for assistance with Air France refunds?</h3>
            <p>For further assistance with cancellations or refunds:</p>
            <p>- Visit the Air France website and submit a refund request.</p>
